🧠 What is NPM?

**NPM (Node Package Manager)** is:

👉 A tool to install and manage JavaScript packages

📌 Comes with Node.js
📌 Largest package ecosystem

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Why NPM is Important?

✔ Reuse existing code
✔ Save development time
✔ Access thousands of libraries
✔ Build scalable applications

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Initialize a Project

```bash
npm init
```

OR quick:

```bash
npm init -y
```

This creates:

```text
package.json
```

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 What is package.json?

It is the **heart of a Node.js project**.

Stores:

✔ Project details
✔ Dependencies
✔ Scripts
✔ Version info

---

Example package.json

```json
{
  "name": "node-project",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "My Node app",
  "main": "app.js",
  "scripts": {
    "start": "node app.js"
  },
  "dependencies": {
    "express": "^4.18.2"
  }
}
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

🔷 Installing Packages

Install package

```bash
npm install express
```

OR:

```bash
npm i express
```

---

Install specific version

```bash
npm install express@4.18.2
```

---

🔷 node_modules Folder

After installing packages:

```text
node_modules/
```

Contains:

✔ All installed packages
✔ Dependencies of dependencies

📌 Automatically created

---

🔷 package-lock.json

This file:

✔ Locks dependency versions
✔ Ensures same installation across systems

---

🔷 Dependencies Types

| Type            | Purpose                |
| --------------- | ---------------------- |
| dependencies    | Required in production |
| devDependencies | Only for development   |

---

## Install dev dependency

```bash
npm install nodemon --save-dev
```

---

🔷 Scripts in package.json

```json
"scripts": {
  "start": "node app.js",
  "dev": "nodemon app.js"
}
```

Run:

```bash
npm run dev
```

---

🔷 Global vs Local Packages

| Type   | Command                |
| ------ | ---------------------- |
| Local  | npm install package    |
| Global | npm install -g package |

Example:

```bash
npm install -g nodemon
```

---

🔷 Uninstall Package

```bash
npm uninstall express
```

---

🔷 Update Package

```bash
npm update
```

---

